Freq: Prior to start of works
Remarks / record (eg. test frequency, reports, certificates, checklist etc):
• Is the fill and base of the foundation compacted to achieve at least 98% and achieving Geotechnical strength as per the design requirements.
• Has the surface shall be thoroughly moistened with water and excess surface water removed prior to placing concrete.
• Formwork has been installed correctly and sufficiently braced.
• Formwork set out has been done as per latest design drawings and specifications
• Were Construction joints/Expansion Joints/Isolation Joints /or any type of joint as specified in the drawings Installed
• Any Backfill/ Underlay Material as per drawings & specifications
• Was Installations of Cast-Ins/ HD bolts/ Chemical Anchors/Block out Verified
• Is the concrete member of height greater than 2m and a formwork design obtained with a certificate of compliance from a Proof Engineer forwarded to the Superintendent for approval?
Freq: Prior to start of works
Remarks / record (eg. test frequency, reports, certificates, checklist etc):
• Tolerance - As per specifications and Australian Standard and minimum cover for steel reinforcement is 40mm.
• Steel is free of excess corrosion, loose millings, oil or other contaminants
• Required Connection details - U Bars/ Z Bars/Cogs Verified/Starter bars
• Correct concrete cover and chairs on sides, bottom and top Verified
• Has steel reinforcement been placed correctly with adequate cover?
• Have tie bars and expansion joints been installed at the correct intervals?
• Pour area is free of loose debris, oils, water
• Have any services located within the slab been installed, surveyed and pinned down
• Concrete Testing Lab Representative will be available during concrete pour
• CYP D&C JV informed of concrete pour date and start time
Freq: Prior to start of each Concrete Pour
• Has concrete been transported, handled and placed to prevent segregation, loss or leakage of materials and air temp within 5 to 35 degrees C
• Has Concrete been tamped/vibrated to increase density and prevent voids, honeycombing or surface defects.
• Has a minimum of one of vibrator used at all times while the concreting is in operation
• Ensure monitoring forms/cast in items during the pour
• Concrete Work(s) completed to specification/drawings & Area left clean/tidy
• Concrete Dockets Received, Attach last Docket
Remarks / record (eg. test frequency, reports, certificates, checklist etc):
• Was Curing agent applies as per project specifications
• Concrete reached design strength to strip formwork
• Any identified defects after striping rectified
• Does Backfill material comply with Vicroad specs, Project specs and drawings?
• Were as Built completed? Attach report if applicable
• Concrete reached design strength to strip formwork. (Attach test results)
• Were expansion joints placed at intervals less than 10m.
Remarks / record (eg. test frequency, reports, certificates, checklist etc):
• Were topsoil placed and compacted on layers not exceeding 150mm in thickness and not exceeding 300mm in width not earlier than 3 days after concrete pour?
• Were the positions of any existing conduits passing under edgings marked by a chase in the edging immediately above the conduit together with a suitable identification mark.
